Matplotlib Library

1- import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


2- plot: this method use to give our x and y
	ex) x = [1, 2, 8]
		y = [8, 2, 5]
		plt.plot(x, y, color='green')


3- for show :
	plt.show()


4- if want to add title to table write:
	plt.title(write title)


5- for x and y label write:
	plt.xlabel(enter x label)
	plt.ylabel(enter y label)



6- if we want show data with dot (.)  and dont write khat
	plt.plot(x, y, 'o', color='green') we can use * replace o


7- if we want show khat and * write
	plt.plot(x,y , marker='*', color='green')


8- if want show data column use bar 
	ex) x = ['red', 'green']
		y = [5, 6]
		plt.bar(x, y)
		plt.show()



9- if want show Circle use pie
	plt.pie(y, labels=x)
	plt.show()

	if want to show percent write
		plt.pie(y, labels=x, autopct="%1.1f", colors=[color list])


10- for show histogram
	ex) x = np.random.rand(1000, 1)
		plt.hist(x)

	** if we want change columns write:
		plt.hist(x, bins=5)


11- for show a matrix we use imshow
	ex) x = np.random.rand(64, 64)
		plt.imshow(x)
		plt.colorbar()
		plt.show()